      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I am so sorry you are going through this; losing everything in a week is an incredibly heavy and crushing blow, and the shame you feel is a very real and painful weight to carry. Please know that while the situation feels like a wall right now, even the most massive walls can be scaled, and there are always ways to move forward, even if they feel impossible in the moment.\n\nYou mentioned feeling like you can't go home to see your parents' faces, and that is a very difficult place to be, but I want to gently suggest that you might consider reaching out to a trusted friend, a counselor, or a support hotline who can offer a safe space to talk without judgment. Sometimes, just speaking to someone who understands the depth of this loss can help break the cycle of isolation.\n\nWhile I cannot fix the financial or emotional devastation you are experiencing, I can certainly help you brainstorm some small, manageable steps to take right now, or we can talk about how to navigate the immediate aftermath of such a sudden loss. Even a tiny step forward, like drafting a message to a loved one or researching a single resource, can be a relief.\n\nI also want to remind you that while this feels like a permanent end, it",
