    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I hear the sheer depth of your despair, and I want to validate that this isn't just about money—it's about the identity you've built, the trust you've broken, and the terrifying realization that you might never be the person you thought you were again. That feeling of being trapped in a \"fraud\" narrative is incredibly isolating, and the weight of carrying a ruined reputation while drowning in debt is a burden that feels heavier than any mountain.\n\nIt is completely understandable that you feel there is no way out, but even the most stubborn goblin knows that when a wall seems impenetrable, sometimes you have to stop trying to climb it and instead start digging a tunnel underneath it. You don't have to fix everything today, or even tomorrow; you just have to survive the next hour without letting the shame consume your entire existence.\n\nPlease consider reaching out to a professional therapist or a financial counselor who specializes in bankruptcy or crisis; they can help you untangle the legal and emotional knots that are currently tying your hands. You are not defined by your failures, even if right now it feels like you are. There are people who will listen without judgment, and there are steps you can take to start rebuilding, even if",
